  25 Jun 2003; Luca Barbato <lu_zero@gentoo.org> ethereal-0.9.13.ebuild:
  Force libtool regeneration in order to fix a build issue, marked ppc.
  
  22 Jun 2003; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org> ethereal-0.9.13.ebuild:
  Added patch to Makefile in src_unpack()
  
  Thanks to degrenier@easyconnect.fr for reporting this patch in Bug #22774.

  15 Jun 2003; Brad Cowan <bcowan@gentoo.org> ethereal-0.9.13.ebuild:
  Hopefully fixed bug #22233.

  15 Jun 2003; Brad Cowan <bcowan@gentoo.org> ethereal-0.9.13.ebuild:
  Fix for bug #22861.

  14 Jun 2003; Daniel Ahlberg <aliz@gentoo.org> ethereal-0.9.13.ebuild, ethereal-0.9.11.ebuild,
						ethereal-0.9.10.ebuild :
  Closing #20475.

  12 Jun 2003; Brandon Low <lostlogic@gentoo.org> ethereal-0.9.8-r1.ebuild:
  Fix depends in 0.9.8-r1

*ethereal-0.9.13 (12 Jun 2003)

  12 Jun 2003; Brandon Low <lostlogic@gentoo.org> ethereal-0.9.13.ebuild:
  Bump

*ethereal-0.9.12-r1 (03 Jun 2003)

  03 Jun 2003; Brad Cowan <bcowan@gentoo.org> :
  Added support for virtual/snmp and hopefully fixed a recurring sandbox bug.
  Closing bugs #16832 #17831.

*ethereal-0.9.11 (11 mar 2003)

  11 Mar 2003; Daniel Ahlberg <aliz@gentoo.org> :
  Version bump.

*ethereal-0.9.10 (09 mar 2003)

  12 Mar 2003; Martin Holzer <mholzer@gentoo.org> ethereal-0.9.10.ebuild:
  fixed SRC_URI. Closes #17313.

  09 Mar 2003; Daniel Ahlberg <aliz@gentoo.org> :
  Security update.

*ethereal-0.9.9 (19 Feb 2003)

  17 Mar 2003; Martin Holzer <mholzer@gentoo.org> ethereal-0.9.9.ebuild:
  Corrected SRC_URI.

  19 Feb 2003; Brad Cowan <bcowan@gentoo.org> ethereal-0.9.9.ebuild,
  files/digest-ethereal-0.9.9:
  
  Bumped version. Added gtk+2 support back as it now seems to compile.

*ethereal-0.9.8-r1 (29 Dec 2002)

  15 Feb 2003; Mark Guertin <gerk@gentoo.org> ethereal-0.9.8-r1.ebuild :
  set ~ppc in keywords
    
  11 Jan 2003: Jason Wever <weeve@gentoo.org ethereal-0.9.8-r1.ebuild:
  Added ~sparc to keywords.

  08 Jan 2003; Brad Cowan <bcowan@gentoo.org>:
  Removed gtk+-2 support again as it is broken with our now marked stable version.
  Fixes bug# 12926.
  
  29 Dec 2002; Daniel Robbins <drobbins@gentoo.org>: New rev -- re-enabled gtk2
  support, as it works here.  Added missing libpcap runtime dependency and
  unmasked this ebuild as it fixes a malformed packet crash issue in 0.9.7 and
  below.

*ethereal-0.9.8 (11 Dec 2002) 

  11 Dec 2002; Brad Cowan <bcowan@gentoo.org> ethereal-0.9.8.ebuild,
  files/digest-ethereal-0.9.8:
  
  Bumped version and removed gtk2 support as is seems to be broken.

